    <item>
      <title>Attention Modeling for Image Captioning</title>
      <link>https://chaitanya100100.github.io/project/attention_modeling_for_image_captioning/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Feb 2019 10:59:14 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>https://chaitanya100100.github.io/project/attention_modeling_for_image_captioning/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Implemented Visual Attention in CNN-RNN architecture for image captioning described in paper 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/abs/1502.03044&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Show, Attend and Tell&lt;/a&gt; achieving the state of the art accuracy on MSCOCO dataset.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Persistent Advantage Learning</title>
      <link>https://chaitanya100100.github.io/project/persistent_advantage_learning/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 20 Feb 2019 10:39:26 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>https://chaitanya100100.github.io/project/persistent_advantage_learning/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Implemented new reinforcement learning operators like advantage learning and persistent advantage learning proposed in paper 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.04860&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Increasing the Action Gap: New Operators for Reinforcement Learning&lt;/a&gt;. Comparative study was done for the performances of advantage learning, persistent advantage learning and Bellman operators with DQN architecture trained on 5 Atari games.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
